            <p class="size26 str500 colorPrimary">General Luna Bridge <br> and its significance:</p>
            <p class="size12">&bull; The General Luna Bridge, also known as Puente Nazas, is a notable landmark in Valdefuente.</p>
            <p class="size12">&bull; It was originally constructed in 1926 but was destroyed in 1941.</p>
            <p class="size12">&bull; The bridge is a truss bridge design, evident from its structural framework.</p>
            <p class="size12">&bull; It played a role in transportation and potentially even railway transport in the past.</p>
            <p class="size12">&bull; A Facebook post shows a photo of the bridge from 1926-1941 and another from 1947 after a temporary wooden truss was installed.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
